# graphic-design / drawbot

DrawBot is a Python 2D-graphics scripting environment: deterministic Python that
calls drawing primitives (rects, ovals, bezier paths, OpenType/variable-font text,
transparency) and exports to PDF, SVG, PNG, GIF, or MP4. OOTA standardizes on
`drawbot-skia` (Apache-2.0, pure-Python, headless CLI) for portable macOS/Linux
rendering — `drawbot script.py out.pdf` runs the script with no GUI and no explicit
saveImage(). The deliverable is a single diffable `.py` script.

controls do
  graphic-design.title: { label: "Title", type: "text" }
  graphic-design.source: { label: "DrawBot script", type: "textarea", file: "src/scene.py" }
end

## Required reading
- DrawBot canonical API reference (original): https://www.drawbot.com/ — no official Anthropic/Claude skill exists.
- drawbot-skia (recommended runtime, Apache-2.0, SUBSET of the API): https://github.com/justvanrossum/drawbot-skia
- Community generative-art skills (structural template only, target p5.js NOT DrawBot): https://github.com/travisvn/awesome-claude-skills

## Render
```bash
pip install drawbot-skia
drawbot src/scene.py out/scene.pdf   # extension selects emitter: pdf|svg|png|mp4
```

## Failure modes
- drawbot-skia implements only a SUBSET of the full drawbot.com API — validate
  scripts against the supported function set, not the full reference.
- Non-determinism: any `random()` must be seeded.
- Text layout depends on the exact font files present — vendor fonts into the repo
  and reference by path, not by installed family name.
- MP4 / advanced OpenType features require the macOS-only original `drawBot`
  module, not drawbot-skia.
- The CLI runs the script as if Run was pressed — do NOT call `saveImage()` in a
  CLI-rendered script; the output path/extension drives the emitter.
